Hey River Children 💖 I am excited to share that me and a bunch of pals went to a river in July and @coleschmidt filmed a little Music Video for UNICORN RIVER CHILD. This song is so personal to me. It is hands down my favourite song. It’s really touched my heart how much love y’all have shown this song. Maybe next Friday would be a good day for a music video?? Thoughts??

Surprise! I dropped a cover of @pleasebeniceyo song “To be Okay” 
We got to work on this cover together. I got to pick the song I wanted to do and it was emphatic choice. I got to sneak into a few sessions for Iris’s album (which is out Friday) and “To Be Okay” made me cry. As someone who has struggled to love their body with all its expansions, contractions, dysphoria, dysmorphia and general deceptions, To Be Okay spoke directly to that complicated nuance, and that’s a testament to Iris as a writer. My friend Iris. WOW. I got some creative liberty on reworking lyrics to fit my story and honestly that’s such a gift. In the words of Iris “THATS SO COOL”
We even got our pal @con.norstagram from @summerhomeband to play guitar on it. 🥰 also obviously Fully Slay Josh Eastman aka @grammywinningnepobaby mixed this track! Love the handle change! Haha! 
Give it a listen. let’s us know what you think!
And if you’re in Vancouver come hang with us at @pleasebeniceyo album release party this Friday.

The lead single off the  17 EP is a song called Seventeen.
If you’ve seen me play in the last few months you would have heard Josh and I play it, it’s a song that lifted me up in a hard time, and helped me find patience and grace for myself and the experiences I never had that left me less equipped than some. I am so excited for you to hear this 80’s Promcore Banger and watch the music video @coleschmidt and I made next Friday! 

Pre-Save in bio! Also come to a show next weekend! Friday or Saturday - tix in bio!

EP IS OUT FRIDAY!!! Pre-Save in bio! 
In a lot of ways the 17 EP is a smattering of songs, the themes lined up as if by accident. 
✨ Kid Wonder is a song I wrote about my friend Kylie, their confidence and kindness don’t hold a flame to the wisdom they offer with love and seek with wild curiosity. They are my Kid Wonder. 
1️⃣7️⃣Seventeen was written in the wake of a breakup. Writing this song with Josh was was healing and special, by the time production started to be added my relationship with the person of focus was shifting and it bloomed into an artifact, a really catchy, fun artifact. 
🔥To be okay was a song from @pleasebeniceyo new album that I loved, the first time I hear it I cried because I really got it “tell me what it feels like to love your body” hit me, so when she asked if I’d cover a song from her album I chose this one and we built it together. Go stream her stuff, it’s really really powerful queer music.
🥰Old Man, the unexpected choice of a cover. Originally we started working on it as a tribute to my grandfather, however as we twisted it into a queer shape it has started to read like a plea to the hetero men of the world who just don’t understand all we as queer people want is the same as them, Love. Thanks Grandpa for being so loving towards me. 🥰
🔥Sister of The Moon was a lost Arcana track that Josh and I love, inspired by my mother and my local queer hero Oliv, it speaks to the power of womanhood and the unshakable spirit of the trans experience. Thank you Oliv for all you have done for me and the rest of the queer babies here in Vancouver and thank you mom for birthing me and loving me. 

I cannot wait for you to hear these tracks, and here your stories about them. I cannot wait to play them live for you. I feel really grateful for you all and I hope you are as excited for the future as I am cuz it’s gonna be amazing and I’d like you to stick along for the ride! 

Photos by @coleschmidt
